issue.body:
See https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/5814

#### Issue details
The current code for getting the screen width always returns the full screen size, even in splitscreen mode
```java
CGRect bounds = app.getBounds();
graphics.width = (int)bounds.getWidth();
graphics.height = (int)bounds.getHeight();
```

The following swing code would get the correct size:
```swing
CGRect windowRect = self.view.window.frame;
CGFloat windowWidth = windowRect.size.width;
CGFloat windowHeight = windowRect.size.height; 
```

body:
The root cause is `IOSApplication.getBounds()` returning the wrong value.
In swift the correct way of getting the actual view size in split screen would be
```
CGRect windowRect = self.view.window.frame;
CGFloat windowWidth = windowRect.size.width;
CGFloat windowHeight = windowRect.size.height;  
```
I think by simply replacing `UIScreen.getMainScreen().getBounds()` with that code the issue could be resolved
